<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-06-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-06-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="102" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d102">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">
                            <persName corresp="#p_LFAWD1">Leahy</persName> Papers: Telegram</note>
                        <head>No. 102 <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Commanding General, United States Military Mission
                                in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_DMGJR1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Deane</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the Commanding General, Twelfth Army Group</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BGON1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Bradley</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                                <lb/>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">urgent</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-06-26">26 June
                                1945</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>To <gloss target="#t_ETOUSA1">ETOUSA</gloss> Forward for <persName corresp="#p_BGON1">Bradley</persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shgsd</hi> and to <gloss target="#t_AGWar1">AGWar</gloss> for <persName corresp="#p_MGAGC1">General
                                Marshall</persName> (<gloss target="#t_EyesOnly1">eyes only</gloss>)
                            from <persName corresp="#p_DMGJR1">Deane</persName> top secret <gloss target="#t_MX1">MX</gloss> 24807.</p>
                        <p>This afternoon again took up the matters raised in <gloss target="#t_S1">S</gloss>–93051<note n="1" xml:id="d102fn1">
                                <ref target="#d96">Document No. 96</ref>.</note> and your <gloss target="#t_S1">S</gloss>–92967 [<hi rend="italic"><gloss target="#t_S1">S</gloss>–92697</hi>]<note n="2" xml:id="d102fn2">
                                <ref target="#d91">Document No. 91</ref>.</note> with <persName corresp="#p_SLGNV1">Lieutenant General Slavin</persName>
                            representing <persName corresp="#p_AAGAI1">General Antonov</persName>. I
                            am hopeful that we will be allowed to send in the communications
                            installation personnel at once and hope to get an official approval by
                            telephone tonight. <persName corresp="#p_SLGNV1">Slavin</persName> asked
                            me how many individuals were involved in the signal communications
                            installation, and rather than delay by sending a cable to you to
                            inquire, I told him 90 persons would be necessary, believing that this
                            would <pb facs="0263" n="131" xml:id="pg_131"/> suffice prior to 1 July,
                            when we can move in as many as desired incident to the occupation of our
                            sector in Berlin. Also hope to get replies on question of reconnoitering
                            Zehlendorf and changing air route from Stendal–Berlin to
                            Halle–Berlin.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>